=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Prepare 5-amino-2-thioxo-4-thiazolidinone (rhodanine-3-amine core precursor), then cyclocondense it with formamide (or formamidine acetate) on heating to build the fused thiazolo[4,5-d]pyrimidin-7-ol intermediate, i.e. 7-hydroxy-2-thioxo-thiazolo[4,5-d]pyrimidin-5-one | Step 2: Convert the 7-OH to the 7-chloro leaving group with POCl3 to give 7-chloro-2-thioxo-thiazolo[4,5-d]pyrimidin-5-one | Step 3: Displace Cl by SNAr with 1-(pyridin-2-yl)piperazine (base, e.g. DIPEA or Et3N, DMF, heat) to furnish 7-(4-(pyridin-2-yl)piperazin-1-yl)-2-thioxo-thiazolo[4,5-d]pyrimidin-5-one | Step 4: Knoevenagel condensation of that activated C5 methylene/lactam intermediate with 4-nitrobenzaldehyde (AcOH or EtOH, catalytic piperidine/ammonium acetate, heat) gives the target 5-(4-nitrobenzylidene)-7-(4-(pyridin-2-yl)piperazin-1-yl)-2-thioxo-thiazolo[4,5-d]pyrimidin-5-one, corresponding to O=C1Nc2cnc(N3CCN(c4ncccn4)CC3)nc2S/C1=C/c1ccc([N+](=O)[O-])cc1.

